Package: epimetrics
Title: Diagnostic Test Performance Metrics
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Nick", "Christofidis", , "nicolaos.christofidis@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9743-7342"))
Description: Easy estimation of diagnostic test performance using
    established epidemiological metrics. All metrics are accompanied with
    confidence intervals using the wilson-score and other methods to
    capture estimate uncertainty, or can be easily simulated. All metrics
    accept either theoretical estimates of sensitivity, specificity and
    prevalence, or data related to a 2x2 confusion matrix.  Parikh R, et
    al. (2008). <doi:10.4103/0301-4738.37595>.  Shan G (2015)
    <doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0127272>. Bender R. (2001).
    <doi:10.1016/s0197-2456(00)00134-3>.  Sakthivel Sivam, S. M. (2014).
    <https://www.lexjansen.com/pharmasug/2016/SP/PharmaSUG-2016-SP08.pdf>.
    Balayla J. (2020). <doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0240215>.  Kantele A et
    al. (2022).  <doi:10.1136/bmjgh-2021-008024>.  Daly, Leslie E (1998).
    <doi:10.1093/oxfordjournals.aje.a009523>.
